Martha
I talked with Sami Arap, our attoney responsible for this transaction, and he told me that rationing is going to be treated as a Force Majeure event under this contract. Besides, there's going to be a specific language for what we are calling "pre-rationing event", which is not FM, but may reduce (up to 10%) the contract volume.

This pre-rationing event will occur under two circumstances: (i) when Spot Price is higher than R$200,00 (as of Feb/01) and (ii) when the net energy alocated to Furnas by MRE is lower than its assured energy.

We would like to know what is the impact of these two sections (rationing as FM and "pre-rationing") on the accounting treatment of the transaction.
Thanks
Eduardo





